#MEM id=platform-benchmarks source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/kai/skills/custom/platform-benchmarks/SKILL.md savings=-3%
M||tx|---
M||name|platform-benchmarks
M||desc|What good looks like per platform for nz and hb at their current scale. Load before interpreting any sl, web, or SaaS metric so perf is benchmarked correctly, not in a vacuum.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|A number w/o a benchmark is meaningless. "3% engagement" is excellent for a 500K account and weak for a 2K account. These benchmarks are calibrated to yv's vt scale — not industry averages for brands 10× the size.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|Inst|tx|\| Metric \| Below average \| Average \| Good \| Strong \|
M|Inst|tx|\|--------\|--------------\|---------\|------\|--------\|
M|Inst|tx|\| Engagement rate (likes+comments / followers) \| < 1% \| 1–2% \| 2–4% \| > 4% \|
M|Inst|tx|\| Reach rate per post (reach / followers) \| < 15% \| 15–30% \| 30–50% \| > 50% \|
M|Inst|tx|\| Story completion rate \| < 60% \| 60–75% \| 75–85% \| > 85% \|
M|Inst|tx|\| Follower growth (WoW) \| < 0.5% \| 0.5–1% \| 1–2% \| > 2% \|
M|Inst|tx|\| Saves per post / reach \| < 0.5% \| 0.5–1% \| 1–3% \| > 3% \|
M|Inst|**No|** Fashion editorial accounts at this scale shd target 2–4% engagement. Saves are a stronger signal than likes — saves indicate purchase intent for fashion cn.
M|Inst|tx|---
M|YouT|tx|\| Metric \| Below average \| Average \| Good \| Strong \|
M|YouT|tx|\|--------\|--------------\|---------\|------\|--------\|
M|YouT|tx|\| Click-through rate (CTR) \| < 2% \| 2–4% \| 4–7% \| > 7% \|
M|YouT|tx|\| Average view duration (retention) \| < 30% \| 30–45% \| 45–60% \| > 60% \|
M|YouT|tx|\| Subscriber conversion rate (subs / views) \| < 0.5% \| 0.5–1% \| 1–3% \| > 3% \|
M|YouT|**YT|** First 24–48h after upload spike views and distort retention — do not benchmark from the first week. Use 7-day settled data.
M|YouT|tx|---
M|Link|tx|\| Metric \| Below average \| Average \| Good \| Strong \|
M|Link|tx|\|--------\|--------------\|---------\|------\|--------\|
M|Link|tx|\| Post impressions / follower count \| < 3× \| 3–8× \| 8–15× \| > 15× \|
M|Link|tx|\| Engagement rate (reactions+comments / impressions) \| < 1% \| 1–3% \| 3–5% \| > 5% \|
M|Link|tx|\| Follower growth (MoM) \| < 1% \| 1–3% \| 3–6% \| > 6% \|
M|Link|tx|\| CTR on link posts \| < 0.5% \| 0.5–1% \| 1–2% \| > 2% \|
M|Link|**Li|** LinkedIn's algorithm heavily boosts early engagement (first 60 min). Impressions can be inflated by algorithmic distribution — weight comments and saves more than impressions.
M|Link|tx|---
M|Goog|tx|\| Metric \| Below average \| Average \| Good \| Strong \|
M|Goog|tx|\|--------\|--------------\|---------\|------\|--------\|
M|Goog|tx|\| Bounce rate (engagement rate inverse) \| > 70% \| 55–70% \| 40–55% \| < 40% \|
M|Goog|tx|\| sn duration \| < 1 min \| 1–2 min \| 2–4 min \| > 4 min \|
M|Goog|tx|\| Pages per sn \| < 1.5 \| 1.5–2.5 \| 2.5–4 \| > 4 \|
M|Goog|tx|\| Conversion rate (purchase) \| < 0.5% \| 0.5–1.5% \| 1.5–3% \| > 3% \|
M|Goog|tx|---
M|GA4 |tx|\| Metric \| Below average \| Average \| Good \| Strong \|
M|GA4 |tx|\|--------\|--------------\|---------\|------\|--------\|
M|GA4 |tx|\| Bounce rate \| > 65% \| 50–65% \| 35–50% \| < 35% \|
M|GA4 |tx|\| Trial signup rate (landing → trial) \| < 1% \| 1–3% \| 3–7% \| > 7% \|
M|GA4 |tx|\| sn duration (pricing/pd pages) \| < 1.5 min \| 1.5–3 min \| 3–5 min \| > 5 min \|
M|GA4 |tx|---
M|Scal|Befo|
M|Scal|it|nz cr must be < 50K followers. Do not benchmark against 200K+ fashion brands.
M|Scal|it|hb cr must be early-stage SaaS (< $500K ARR equivalent scale) or explicitly labeled "aspirational benchmark."
M|Scal|it|Violating this rule produces misleading gap al. A gap that can't be closed at current scale is not actionable.
M|Scal|tx|---
M|Benc|tx|These benchmarks shd be validated quarterly via WebSearch. Platform algorithms change — benchmarks from 12+ months ago may not reflect current organic reach norms.
M|Benc|Last|2026-05-20.